CatDescriptText: B.T. Rankin, steelworker, 1841 Colwell Street and Flossie Latney, laundry worker, 619 Junilla Street, were part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 5, 1959, pg. A1
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of B.T. Rankin wearing moustache, angled hat, dark shirt with light colored buttons, and light colored rain jacket, posed in front of brick wall; Portrait of Flossie Latney wearing grid patterned coat with single button at neck, light colored fringed scarf at neck, and purse strap over shoulder, standing in front of brick building
